text: Procanthopterygii is a superorder of teleost fishes. These fish mostly live in temperate waters, and in the northern hemisphere. They may live in both fresh and salt water. Best-known examples of this group are the salmon, trout, and pikes. The main groups are: * Argentiniformes * Esociformes * Osmeriformes * Salmoniformes == References == Category:Teleosts
title: Protacanthopterygii
